<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFD4334DFF52FB23730CF9E4" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFD4334DFF52FB23730CF9E4" blockId="12.[166,1226,1114,1852]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized among other 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC1DFB2376B5FB64" box="[916,1158,1249,1276]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC1DFB23761FFB63" box="[916,1068,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Campylocera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from the long pedicel and flagellomere 1 parallel-sided, apically bluntly rounded, fore femur with moderately long and thin setae, but without thickened apicoventral setae on dorsal surface, mid coxa with row of strong setae (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFD37FA83713FFAC4" box="[702,780,1345,1372]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[174,207,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[303,1111,182,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-134@13.[298,1112,174,1300]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 14. Campylocera angustipalpis: holotype ♀ (MNKB): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left; 4 — same, anterior; 5 — same, dorsal view; 6 —mesonotum, dorsal view; 7 — prosternum and fore coxae; 8 — fore leg, posterior view; 9 — mid femur, anterior; 10 — mid coxa; 11 — hind femur, anterior view; 12 — hind coxae; 13 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 14 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453730/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">fig. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFC92FA837104FAC3" box="[795,823,1345,1371]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[166,199,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[255,1063,1151,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-429@10.[246,1073,1138,1759]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 10. Campylocera latigenis: holotype Ơ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, right; 4 — head, dorsal view; 5 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453716/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC92FA837104FAC3" box="[795,823,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) hind coxa antero-ventrally with somewhat thickened spinulose setulae (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFDFCFAA370F3FAE4" box="[629,704,1377,1404]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[174,207,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[303,1111,182,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-134@13.[298,1112,174,1300]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 14. Campylocera angustipalpis: holotype ♀ (MNKB): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left; 4 — same, anterior; 5 — same, dorsal view; 6 —mesonotum, dorsal view; 7 — prosternum and fore coxae; 8 — fore leg, posterior view; 9 — mid femur, anterior; 10 — mid coxa; 11 — hind femur, anterior view; 12 — hind coxae; 13 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 14 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453730/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">fig. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFD45FAA370DBFAE3" box="[716,744,1377,1403]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[166,199,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[255,1063,1151,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-429@10.[246,1073,1138,1759]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 10. Campylocera latigenis: holotype Ơ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, right; 4 — head, dorsal view; 5 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453716/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFD45FAA370DBFAE3" box="[716,744,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) not forming comb or thick brush; veins brown bordered, cell R 
<subScript id="C26E5C32FFD4334DFE30FA5673E7FA3A" attach="left" box="[441,468,1428,1442]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">2+3</subScript>
apically with narrow brown apical margin (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFC6AFA43761CFA04" box="[995,1071,1409,1436]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[174,207,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[303,1111,182,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-134@13.[298,1112,174,1300]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 14. Campylocera angustipalpis: holotype ♀ (MNKB): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left; 4 — same, anterior; 5 — same, dorsal view; 6 —mesonotum, dorsal view; 7 — prosternum and fore coxae; 8 — fore leg, posterior view; 9 — mid femur, anterior; 10 — mid coxa; 11 — hind femur, anterior view; 12 — hind coxae; 13 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 14 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453730/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">fig. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFBB4FA437678FA03" box="[1085,1099,1409,1435]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1748,1770]" captionTargetBox="[272,1113,774,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-10@3.[272,1122,774,1719]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Campylocera ferruginea: holotype ♀ of Campylocera omissa (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 3 — head, anterior view; 4 —wing; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior view (arrow indicates long setae); 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior view; 9–10 — oviscape, dorsal and left view; 11 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453690/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFBB4FA437678FA03" box="[1085,1099,1409,1435]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), oviscape long and narrow, without peculiar modified structures (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFCBBFA63714EFA24" box="[818,893,1441,1468]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[174,207,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[303,1111,182,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-134@13.[298,1112,174,1300]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 14. Campylocera angustipalpis: holotype ♀ (MNKB): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left; 4 — same, anterior; 5 — same, dorsal view; 6 —mesonotum, dorsal view; 7 — prosternum and fore coxae; 8 — fore leg, posterior view; 9 — mid femur, anterior; 10 — mid coxa; 11 — hind femur, anterior view; 12 — hind coxae; 13 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 14 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453730/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">fig. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFC01FA6371A5FA23" box="[904,918,1441,1467]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,680,702]" captionTargetBox="[280,1119,174,659]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[272,1122,174,674]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Campylocera ferruginea, holotype (MHNP): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 4 — head, anterior view; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453688/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC01FA6371A5FA23" box="[904,918,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD4334DFC2AFA63718CFA23" box="[931,959,1441,1467]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,563,585]" captionTargetBox="[364,1037,174,533]" captionTargetId="figure-541@12.[342,1049,167,562]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 13. Campylocera latigenis: holotype ♀ Dicrostyra partitigena (NHMW): 1 — abdomen, ventral; 2 — oviscape, right; 3 — apex of oviscape, right, enlarged; 4 — aculeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453728/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC2AFA63718CFA23" box="[931,959,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">13</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum without presutural supra-alar setae; scutellum short setulose, 2 setae on each side. Th is species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFEF8FA23704DFA64" authority="Hendel 1914" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[369,638,1505,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFEF8FA2373B7FA63" box="[369,388,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFE18FA2373D0FA63" box="[401,483,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">gracilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFE60FA23704DFA64" author="Hendel, F." box="[489,638,1505,1532]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="77 - 117" refId="ref11510" refString="Hendel, F. 1914. Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pyrgotinen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (11) (1913), 77 - 117 + 1 Taf." type="journal article" year="1914">Hendel 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Southern 
<collectingCountry id="26FD1EE7FFD4334DFCB0FA2371A3FA64" box="[825,912,1505,1532]" name="Nigeria" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
differing mainly by longer setulose fore femur (short setulose with short, slightly thickened setulae apicoventrally in 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFF2FF9E3732BF9A3" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[166,280,1569,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFF2FF9E3728AF9A3" box="[166,185,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFF4FF9E3732BF9A3" box="[198,280,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Study of additional material is necessary to clarify, if this is a reliable difference of species or individual variability. No reliable associations with males found in collections are available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFD4334CFF52F9437398F88A" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="208" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFD4334CFF52F9437398F88A" blockId="12.[166,1226,1114,1852]" lastBlockId="13.[174,1233,1481,1810]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="208" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">
R e m a r k. 
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFEEBF9437018F904" author="Enderlein, G." box="[354,555,1665,1692]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="98 - 134" refId="ref11407" refString="Enderlein, G. 1942. Klassifikation der Pyrgotiden. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschenden Freunde zu Berlin, (1941) (2), 98 - 134." type="journal article" year="1942">Enderlein (1942)</bibRefCitation>
originally recognized 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFCB2F9437199F903" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[827,938,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Clemaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCB2F9437199F903" box="[827,938,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Clemaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a genus to place the flies with incomplete costa, vein M reaching wing margin, R 
<subScript id="C26E5C32FFD4334DFCEBF976714FF95A" attach="left" box="[866,892,1716,1730]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">2+3</subScript>
with or without stump vein, and scutellum bearing 4 setae. In this paper, all the Old World 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC21F903761CF944" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[936,1071,1729,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Adapsiliina">Adapsiliina</taxonomicName>
species with incomplete costa are lumped in a monophyletic genus 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFC91F9237183F963" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[792,944,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFC91F9237183F963" box="[792,944,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I therefore synonymize both generic names. Within 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFE70F8C370A2F883" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[505,657,1793,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFE70F8C370A2F883" box="[505,657,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFD29F8C37169F883" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[672,858,1793,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Clemaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipalpis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFD29F8C37080F883" box="[672,691,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFD48F8C37169F883" box="[705,858,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">angustipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a small group of species together with 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFED8F8E37042F8A4" authority="(Hendel, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[337,625,1825,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Hypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewi">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFED8F8E37357F8A3" box="[337,356,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFEFCF8E37382F8A3" box="[373,433,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">loewi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFE4AF8E3705BF8A4" author="Hendel, F." box="[451,616,1825,1852]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref11436" refString="Hendel, F. 1908. Acht neue Pyrgotinen (Dipt.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 27 (4 - 5), 145 - 153." type="journal article" year="1908">Hendel, 1908</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFD09F8E370C6F8A3" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[640,757,1825,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFD09F8E370A0F8A3" box="[640,659,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFD2AF8E370C6F8A3" box="[675,757,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD4334DFCB5F8E3764EF8A4" authority="(Hendel, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[828,1149,1825,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Hypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCB5F8E3717CF8A3" box="[828,847,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD4334DFCE9F8E3718DF8A3" box="[864,958,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="207">caudata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFD4334DFC59F8E37646F8A4" author="Hendel, F." box="[976,1141,1825,1852]" pageId="12" pageNumber="207" pagination="77 - 117" refId="ref11510" refString="Hendel, F. 1914. Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pyrgotinen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (11) (1913), 77 - 117 + 1 Taf." type="journal article" year="1914">Hendel, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; these species share elongate and narrow pedicel, elongate and blunt flagellomere 1, small or moderately developed ocellar triangle with 1–2 pairs of ocellar setae, mid and hind coxae of females with more or less thickened setae, and oviscape narrow and long, 1.3–2 times as long as abdominal tergites combined and no sclerotized lobes or long sensillar brushes or combs at its apical aperture. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD5334CFDBDF9A270C3F9E2" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[564,752,1632,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Clemaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipalpis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFDBDF9A27074F9E2" box="[564,583,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFDDEF9A270C3F9E2" box="[599,752,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">angustipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from superficially 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD5334CFF27F9447314F907" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[174,295,1669,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFF27F94472F2F938" box="[174,193,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFF5CF9477314F907" box="[213,295,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which shares similarly setulose mid and hind coxae of females, by the long and fine setae of the ventral rows on fore femur (the basalmost seta twice as long as femur width), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD5334CFE1FF9137039F973" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[406,522,1745,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFE1FF913739AF973" box="[406,425,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD5334CFE31F9137039F973" box="[440,522,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are short and spurious (the basalmost seta at most as long as femur width).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
